  "text": "TAGLN2 is a tumor suppressor in pancreatic cancer [CITATION_1] , but silencing of the TAGLN2 gene significantly inhibits cell proliferation and invasion in head and neck squamous cell carcinoma [CITATION_2] . However, the lncRNAs analyzed in our study should be distinguished from transcripts, and the function of lncRNAs has yet to be determined.",
